	HELP CONSOLE
1. --ip <IP Address>: 		Used to enter a single IP to be scanned.
				e.g. --ip 127.79.54.79

2. --prefix <IP Subnet/Size>:	Used to enter the prefix range to be. 
				scanned e.g. --ip 127.79.54.0/24

3. --ports <PORT NO.>	:	Port numbers can be entered as a single
   or				port or a range of ports or multiple ports 
   --ports <PORT 1 - PORT 2>	seperated by comma.
   or				e.g. --ports 80, --ports 80,81
   --ports <PORT 1, PORT2>

4. --scan <scan-type>	:	Used to enter scan types.
				e.g. --scan SYN

5. --speedup <no. of threads>:	Used to specify the maximum number
				of threads.
				e.g. --speedup 2

6. --file <file_name>	:	Used to enter the file name from which 
				the program will read the IP address's to
				scan.
				e.g. --file ip_file

7. --protocol-range <ptotocols>:Used to enter the protocols to be scanned
				for Protocol Scan.
				e.g. --protocol-range 1-20
